Subject: Re: [T2] Oil drain plug won't tighten

I go one step further when I do this, and slowly flush about 1 qt kerosene
down the fill with the plug out after retapping just to rinse out shavings,
which you may very well find in the pan.  Then I usually flush about a 1/2 qt
of cheap (even used) oil through as well and put in the new oversized plug and
refill.

The rubber expander plugs actually can give fair service as well for
a massively overstripped plug.

John


