From:
Mike Soultanian mike.soultanian(-at-)csulb.edu

store and pick up a self-tapping
oversized oil drain plug and carefully retap the hole.  I had to do that with
mine and I coated the bolt with a lot of grease and carefully screwed it in a
little till it started cutting a few threads, backed it out, cleaned it off,
more grease, screwed it in a little more, backed it out, cleaned, greased, and
repeat.
